The start tag is often called the opening tag. The end tag is often called the closing tag.
Only the <body> area (the white area) is displayed by the browser.
<!DOCTYPE> The doctype declaration is not case sensitive.
You can use either .htm or .html as file extension. There is no difference, it is up to you.
Some HTML elements do not have an end tag.
<br> is an empty element without a closing tag (the <br> tag defines a line break).
HTML tags are not case sensitive: recommends lowercase in HTML4, and demands lowercase for stricter document types like XHTML.
Attributes are always specified in the start tag.
recommends quotes in HTML4, and demands quotes for stricter document types like XHTML.
